cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on word embeddings and their use in capturing semantic shifts across time and geography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural network-based models, which are a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves training a neural language model, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of embeddings to improve results in various applications such as document classification and named entity recognition suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of enhanced scatterplots and storyline visualization, which could fall under cs.DL (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
